In a statement, President Obama congratulated King Abdullah and the Saudi people on the selection of Prince Nayif bin Abd al-Aziz Al Saud as Crown Prince and Deputy Prime Minister of Saudi Arabia. The President highlighted Prince Nayif's long and dedicated service to the nation, particularly as Minister of Interior and Second Deputy Prime Minister. The United States values Prince Nayif's commitment to combating terrorism and promoting regional peace and security. The President expressed his desire to continue the strong partnership between the United States and Saudi Arabia under Prince Nayif's leadership.